# Econic Graphs Monorepo

This workspace contains the source code and documentation for a multi-layered framework enabling developers to build interactive 3D graph visualisations in the browser.

## Project Structure

```
graphs/
├── docs/                    # Project documentation (ONLY place for docs)
│   └── Project-scope.md     # Architecture and API specifications
├── graph-core/              # Rust/WASM - WebGPU rendering engine
├── graph-3d/                # TypeScript - Buffer orchestration & overlays
├── graph-morph/             # TypeScript - Meta-graph & transitions
└── graph-ui/                # TypeScript - Framework bindings (Future)
```

## Documentation Rules

- **All documentation must be placed in `/docs`** - this is the single source of truth for project documentation
- Do not create README files in subprojects beyond the minimal project-specific README
- API documentation belongs in `/docs`, not scattered across packages
- Each package README should be brief and link to `/docs` for detailed information

## Package Dependencies (Layered Architecture)

```
Layer 4: graph-ui      → graph-morph
Layer 3: graph-morph   → graph-3d  
Layer 2: graph-3d      → graph-core
Layer 1: graph-core    → (WebGPU)
```

## Development Notes

- `graph-core` is Rust/WASM - use `cargo` and `wasm-pack`
- `graph-3d`, `graph-morph`, `graph-ui` are TypeScript - use `pnpm`
- Each package is a separate git repository
- Coordinate system uses Normalised Device Coordinates (NDC): -1 to 1 on each axis

## Package Naming

NPM packages use the `@econic/` scope:
- `@econic/graph-core`
- `@econic/graph-3d`
- `@econic/graph-morph`
- `@econic/graph-ui`
